  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil in a medium skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add cumin, chili powder, and paprika and cook for 1 minute more.",
    "Add haggis and cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks.",
    "Stir in vegetable broth and bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce heat to low and cook for 5 minutes.",
    "Warm tortillas by wrapping them in a damp paper towel and microwaving for 20-30 seconds.",
    "Spoon haggis mixture onto tortillas and top with a spoonful of horchata.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro and crushed red pepper.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
